Matt, Will and Tiger are predicting the outcome of a tournament, which only has $$4$$ teams.  \textbf{Matt: "Team $$A$$ will be the $$1$$\textsuperscript{st}, and Team $$B$$ will be the $$4$$\textsuperscript{th}."~}  \textbf{Will: "Team $$B$$ will be the $$2$$\textsuperscript{nd}, and Team $$C$$ will be the $$3$$\textsuperscript{rd}."}  \textbf{Tiger: "Team $$A$$ will be the $$2$$\textsuperscript{nd}, and Team $$D$$ will be the $$4$$\textsuperscript{th}."}  After the tournament, it turns out they are all half-right and half-wrong. What is the ranking of Team $$D$$?
(A) 1$$\textsuperscript{st}
(B) 2$$\textsuperscript{nd}
(C) 3$$\textsuperscript{rd}
(D) 4$$\textsuperscript{th}

2019 AMC 8/ Problem 18  The faces of each of two fair dice are numbered 1, 2, 3, 5, 7 and 8. When the two dice are tossed, what is the probability that their sum will be an even number?
(A) \dfrac{4}{9}
(B) \dfrac{1}{2}
(C) \dfrac{5}{9}
(D) \dfrac{3}{5}
(E) \dfrac{2}{3}
